a necklace like that.

527
00:19:40.347 --> 00:19:41.648
where would I get it?

528
00:19:41.781 --> 00:19:43.916
Nepal. at a puja ceremony.

529
00:19:44.016 --> 00:19:45.752
Puja.
Mm-hmm.

530
00:19:45.852 --> 00:19:48.120
At the base of Everest.
You know about it?

531
00:19:48.255 --> 00:19:51.157
A Tibetan lama blesses the climb

532
00:19:51.291 --> 00:19:53.360
before you go up the mountain.
right?

533
00:19:53.493 --> 00:19:54.494
That's right. Yeah.
Ah.

534
00:19:54.627 --> 00:19:55.662
He gave me this.

535
00:19:55.795 --> 00:19:57.464
Wait. you've climbed Everest?

536
00:19:57.597 --> 00:19:59.165
Not quite.
Got most of the way up.

537
00:19:59.299 --> 00:20:00.467
then another team
got in trouble.

538
00:20:00.600 --> 00:20:02.502
We had to help them down.

539
00:20:02.635 --> 00:20:05.472
Then some bad weather set in.
and that was that.

540
00:20:05.605 --> 00:20:06.706
You climb?

541
00:20:06.839 --> 00:20:08.941
No. I wish.

542
00:20:09.041 --> 00:20:10.710
I'm just interested.

543
00:20:10.843 --> 00:20:12.712
Man. to get that close
to the top

544
00:20:12.845 --> 00:20:13.846
and not make it.

545
00:20:13.980 --> 00:20:15.448
That's got to be hard.

546
00:20:15.548 --> 00:20:16.883
When you're on the mountain.
you're not in control.

547
00:20:17.016 --> 00:20:18.217
The mountain is.

548
00:20:18.351 --> 00:20:19.886
Just got to accept it.

549
00:20:20.019 --> 00:20:21.621
Who says?

550
00:20:24.857 --> 00:20:26.058
One more!

551
00:20:26.192 --> 00:20:28.395
Yeah. I'm afraid that's it.

552
00:20:28.528 --> 00:20:29.696
Wait. wait. N-No.

553
00:20:29.829 --> 00:20:31.298
You're cutting me off?

554
00:20:31.398 --> 00:20:32.399
Let me get you a cab.

555
00:20:32.532 --> 00:20:33.733
Ah.

556
00:20:33.866 --> 00:20:35.502
No. thank you.

557
00:20:35.635 --> 00:20:37.169
Let me. You've had
a bit too much to drink.
No.

558
00:20:37.304 --> 00:20:39.238
I'm nothing. Okay? I'm great.

559
00:20:39.372 --> 00:20:42.575
I won the lottery this morning.
That's how I got this.

560
00:20:42.709 --> 00:20:43.876
You said you hurt it
playing racquetball.

561
00:20:44.010 --> 00:20:45.412
Whatever. man. I am fine.

562
00:20:45.545 --> 00:20:47.680
I don't need your help.
I'm fine.

563
00:20:47.814 --> 00:20:49.582
Okay. You're fine.

564
00:20:52.685 --> 00:20:56.188
♪ All together now.

565
00:20:56.323 --> 00:20:59.258
Uh. thanks. Taylor.
Text me if anything pops up.

566
00:20:59.392 --> 00:21:01.494
They leaked it.
What?

567
00:21:01.594 --> 00:21:03.029
Our settlement offer.

568
00:21:03.162 --> 00:21:04.764
Retaliation for
the press conference. I bet.

569
00:21:04.897 --> 00:21:06.999
They're trying to make Raiden
look like a saint.

570
00:21:07.099 --> 00:21:09.235
like he walked away
from $7 million

571
00:21:09.369 --> 00:21:10.770
to protect future victims.

572
00:21:10.903 --> 00:21:12.505
They're gonna see this.
and going after him

573
00:21:12.605 --> 00:21:13.940
about overdue
child support payments

574
00:21:14.073 --> 00:21:15.608
isn't gonna move
the needle.
Yep.

575
00:21:15.742 --> 00:21:17.744
Seven million would buy
a lot of school lunches.

576
00:21:17.877 --> 00:21:19.579
Please tell me that
Taylor found some connection

577
00:21:19.712 --> 00:21:22.081
between Raiden and one of
Moore House Tech's competitors.

578
00:21:22.214 --> 00:21:24.116
No obvious link.

579
00:21:24.250 --> 00:21:26.419
Uh. Raiden mainly worked
in academia

580
00:21:26.553 --> 00:21:27.887
before the Moore House Tech gig.

581
00:21:28.020 --> 00:21:29.522
What about Danny?
Anything from the bar?

582
00:21:29.622 --> 00:21:33.125
No one willing to say that
Raiden targeted Kyla directly.

583
00:21:34.427 --> 00:21:36.596
Just gonna have to go after
Raiden with what I got.

584
00:21:36.729 --> 00:21:38.398
Which is?

585
00:21:38.531 --> 00:21:40.467
My wit and charm.

586
00:21:41.801 --> 00:21:44.637
It took me a long time
to admit I was being harassed.

587
00:21:44.771 --> 00:21:46.373
Abused.

588
00:21:46.473 --> 00:21:49.376
As a man. that's a hard thing
to wrap your head around.

589
00:21:49.476 --> 00:21:53.380
But my therapist helped me work
up the courage to confront Kyla.

590
00:21:53.480 --> 00:21:56.248
So I told her
I wasn't gonna meet her

591
00:21:56.383 --> 00:21:57.817
in her hotel suite anymore.

592
00:21:57.950 --> 00:22:00.587
And did the defendant accept no
for an answer?

593
00:22:00.720 --> 00:22:02.321
No.

594
00:22:02.455 --> 00:22:03.656
That's when she started coming
to the satellite office

595
00:22:03.790 --> 00:22:04.957
where I was working.

596
00:22:05.091 --> 00:22:07.494
She'd corner me
and demand that I go

597
00:22:07.627 --> 00:22:10.463
into the storage closet
with her and...

598
00:22:13.132 --> 00:22:15.301
...perform oral sex on her.

599
00:22:17.136 --> 00:22:19.839
That's not true.
Try not to react.

600
00:22:19.972 --> 00:22:22.274
Why not simply refuse
to go in the closet with her?

601
00:22:22.409 --> 00:22:23.843
She said if I didn't give her
what she wanted.

602
00:22:23.976 --> 00:22:25.277
she'd fire me.

603
00:22:25.412 --> 00:22:26.613
I needed the job.

604
00:22:26.746 --> 00:22:28.781
But I started having
these panic attacks.

605
00:22:28.915 --> 00:22:29.782
worrying about

606
00:22:29.916 --> 00:22:31.518
when she'd come for me next.

607
00:22:31.651 --> 00:22:33.686
So eventually I did refuse.

608
00:22:33.820 --> 00:22:37.256
And true to her word.
she fired me.

609
00:22:37.356 --> 00:22:40.159
Why did you decide
to bring this lawsuit?

610
00:22:40.292 --> 00:22:42.328
I have two young sons.

611
00:22:42.462 --> 00:22:44.431
I just can't stand the thought
that someone could do this

612
00:22:44.531 --> 00:22:45.998
to one of them someday.

613
00:22:46.132 --> 00:22:47.834
I couldn't stay silent.

614
00:22:47.967 --> 00:22:49.669
No further questions.
Your Honor.

615
00:22:50.637 --> 00:22:53.039
We just lost another one.

616
00:22:53.172 --> 00:22:55.708
Should I even look?

617
00:22:55.842 --> 00:22:57.844
That depends. Are you
a glutton for punishment?

618
00:22:57.977 --> 00:23:00.847
I'm a grown man.

619
00:23:00.980 --> 00:23:03.182
using a foam roller
on the floor

620
00:23:03.315 --> 00:23:04.684
in front of my employees.

621
00:23:04.817 --> 00:23:07.119
I'm a glutton for something.

622
00:23:07.219 --> 00:23:09.489
You said that
Kyla Moore fired you.

623
00:23:09.622 --> 00:23:11.624
But. in fact.
you left Moore House Tech

624
00:23:11.724 --> 00:23:13.192
when your six-month contract

625
00:23:13.325 --> 00:23:15.662
as a freelance coder
came to its natural end.

626
00:23:15.795 --> 00:23:16.829
Isn't that correct?

627
00:23:16.963 --> 00:23:18.565
Well. I was hired
as a freelancer.

628
00:23:18.698 --> 00:23:20.800
But when Kyla coerced me
into sleeping with her.

629
00:23:20.900 --> 00:23:23.736
she promised she'd make
my position permanent.

630
00:23:23.870 --> 00:23:26.639
When I broke things off.
that went away.

631
00:23:26.739 --> 00:23:30.009
Do you have any written proof
that Ms. Moore altered

632
00:23:30.142 --> 00:23:31.978
the terms of
your employment contract?

633
00:23:32.078 --> 00:23:34.747
No.
Do you have any proof
that she forced you

634
00:23:34.881 --> 00:23:36.549
in a supply closet?

635
00:23:36.683 --> 00:23:38.150
Security camera footage.
perhaps?

636
00:23:38.250 --> 00:23:39.686
It was her company.
I mean. she knew

637
00:23:39.819 --> 00:23:41.521
how to avoid the cameras.
What about witnesses?

638
00:23:41.654 --> 00:23:44.090
If she came to your workspace
as frequently as you claim.

639
00:23:44.223 --> 00:23:45.492
surely one of your colleagues

640
00:23:45.592 --> 00:23:46.726
would've seen
the two of you together?

641
00:23:46.859 --> 00:23:48.861
She was always very careful.

642
00:23:48.995 --> 00:23:50.196
Having sex

643
00:23:50.329 --> 00:23:52.064
in a supply closet at work

644
00:23:52.198 --> 00:23:53.533
doesn't sound careful to me.

645
00:23:53.666 --> 00:23:55.768
No. in fact. Mr. Parks.

646
00:23:55.902 --> 00:23:59.238
it sounds to me like your story
just doesn't add up.

647
00:23:59.371 --> 00:24:00.673
Objection. Inflammatory.

648
00:24:00.773 --> 00:24:01.941
Counsel is testifying.

649
00:24:02.074 --> 00:24:03.275
Sustained.

650
00:24:03.409 --> 00:24:05.211
Watch your step. Mr. Palmer.

651
00:24:05.344 --> 00:24:06.746
Mr. Parks. you don't have

652
00:24:06.879 --> 00:24:08.515
a single shred of evidence
that proves

653
00:24:08.615 --> 00:24:10.683
that Ms. Moore knew
you were her employee

654
00:24:10.783 --> 00:24:12.952
when you were having a
consensual sexual relationship.

655
00:24:13.085 --> 00:24:13.953
do you?

656
00:24:14.086 --> 00:24:15.221
Yes. I do.

657
00:24:16.455 --> 00:24:18.424
I have her email.

658
00:24:20.927 --> 00:24:22.128
Your Honor.

659
00:24:22.261 --> 00:24:23.596
we went through
Ms. Moore's emails

660
00:24:23.730 --> 00:24:26.566
and there wasn't
a single email to Mr. Parks.

661
00:24:26.699 --> 00:24:28.100
Your Honor.

662
00:24:28.234 --> 00:24:30.102
I have the email
in question right here.

663
00:24:30.236 --> 00:24:35.407
It's from Kittyky1999@AOL.com

664
00:24:35.542 --> 00:24:37.577
from the defendant's
personal account.

665
00:24:37.710 --> 00:24:39.311
I haven't used that account
since college.

666
00:24:39.445 --> 00:24:40.913
It's where I send
all my spam.

667
00:24:41.047 --> 00:24:42.715
The plaintiff did not provide
any of these

668
00:24:42.815 --> 00:24:45.117
for discovery. and we have not
had a chance to review it.

669
00:24:45.251 --> 00:24:47.153
Defense has access to
their client's

670
00:24:47.286 --> 00:24:48.655
personal emails.

671
00:24:48.788 --> 00:24:50.489
It's not Mr. Parks' fault
that they missed it.

672
00:24:50.623 --> 00:24:52.324
Your Honor...
And Mr. Palmer asked

673
00:24:52.458 --> 00:24:53.793
if Mr. Parks has proof.

674
00:24:53.926 --> 00:24:55.795
He should be allowed
to present his proof.

675
00:25:01.400 --> 00:25:02.769
I'll allow it.

676
00:25:06.338 --> 00:25:07.640
Go ahead. Mr. Parks.

677
00:25:07.774 --> 00:25:10.076
"Ray. I can't stop
thinking about you.

678
00:25:10.176 --> 00:25:11.644
"I've never felt this way
for anyone.

679
00:25:11.778 --> 00:25:13.846
not even my husband."

680
00:25:13.980 --> 00:25:15.114
I didn't write that.

681
00:25:15.247 --> 00:25:16.182
That's not me.

682
00:25:16.315 --> 00:25:17.483
"I need you right now.

683
00:25:17.617 --> 00:25:19.418
"Meet me at the Arlo
in an hour.

684
00:25:19.518 --> 00:25:20.820
"Don't say no this time.

685
00:25:20.953 --> 00:25:23.322
or I'll be forced
to punish you at work."

686
00:25:27.326 --> 00:25:28.595
I'm done defending you.

687
00:25:28.695 --> 00:25:30.296
Oscar.

688
00:25:30.429 --> 00:25:31.964
I want order in this court.

689
00:25:34.133 --> 00:25:35.467
Order!
What's happening?

690
00:25:35.602 --> 00:25:37.604
Oh. son of a bitch.

691
00:25:38.671 --> 00:25:39.639
Was this the email you pulled?

692
00:25:39.772 --> 00:25:40.940
I need to go after Kyla.

693
00:25:41.040 --> 00:25:42.041
Order!

694
00:25:42.174 --> 00:25:44.376
Marissa.
Taylor. talk to me.

695
00:25:44.510 --> 00:25:46.278
Mr. Palmer.
get control of your client.
Tell me what's happening.

696
00:25:46.378 --> 00:25:48.214
Pretty sure
all hell is breaking loose.

697
00:25:56.022 --> 00:25:57.624
I have never
seen Oscar that angry.

698
00:25:57.724 --> 00:26:00.660
Well. that's probably him.

699
00:26:02.194 --> 00:26:04.563
No. The board is meeting
to discuss my position.

700
00:26:04.697 --> 00:26:05.798
They want me to resign.

701
00:26:05.898 --> 00:26:07.533
Just go home. lay low.

702
00:26:07.667 --> 00:26:09.335
We will get to the bottom
of all of this.

703
00:26:09.468 --> 00:26:11.370
Thank you.

704
00:26:14.173 --> 00:26:16.208
Take me home.

705
00:26:20.079 --> 00:26:21.247
If you're trying
to protect your friend.

706
00:26:21.380 --> 00:26:22.815
you're doing a lousy job.

707
00:26:22.915 --> 00:26:24.316
What?

708
00:26:24.416 --> 00:26:26.418
You pulled that email
from discovery. didn't you?

709
00:26:26.552 --> 00:26:28.054
Do you think I am that stupid?

710
00:26:28.187 --> 00:26:30.823
To try and cover up an email
the other side received?

711
00:26:30.923 --> 00:26:32.191
I know you're hiding something.

712
00:26:32.324 --> 00:26:33.760
You pulled an email.
What was it?

713
00:26:33.893 --> 00:26:36.996
It was an email
I wrote about you. okay?

714
00:26:37.096 --> 00:26:38.865
What?

715
00:26:38.998 --> 00:26:41.834
I pulled it because
I was trying to protect you.

716
00:26:41.934 --> 00:26:43.770
After Benny left.
I emailed Kyla

717
00:26:43.903 --> 00:26:45.571
to see if she knew
any good attorneys.

718
00:26:45.705 --> 00:26:48.440
I wasn't sure if you were up
to the job of chief counsel.

719
00:26:49.441 --> 00:26:50.542
You have doubts
about my abilities?

720
00:26:50.677 --> 00:26:52.411
I did. then.

721
00:26:52.544 --> 00:26:55.381
I don't anymore. but clearly you
have doubts about my integrity.

722
00:26:55.514 --> 00:26:57.449
It's my ass that's on the line
as the lawyer.

723
00:26:57.583 --> 00:26:59.451
and Kyla is your friend.

724
00:26:59.585 --> 00:27:01.087
People do stupid stuff
for their friends.

725
00:27:01.220 --> 00:27:02.254
Clearly.

726
00:27:02.388 --> 00:27:03.690
Look. just next time

727
00:27:03.790 --> 00:27:05.725
give me a little bit of credit.
okay?

728
00:27:05.858 --> 00:27:07.393
My ego is not that fragile.

729
00:27:07.526 --> 00:27:09.361
Okay.

730
00:27:09.461 --> 00:27:11.130
Done.

731
00:27:14.433 --> 00:27:16.635
Kyla didn't write that email.
you know.

732
00:27:16.769 --> 00:27:18.237
If she didn't write it.
who did?

733
00:27:18.370 --> 00:27:19.972
Raiden or whoever
he's working for.

734
00:27:20.106 --> 00:27:21.440
Think about it.

735
00:27:21.573 --> 00:27:23.475
Why would Kyla tell us
about those videos

736
00:27:23.609 --> 00:27:24.744
but hide that email?

737
00:27:24.877 --> 00:27:26.045
It's the smoking gun.

738
00:27:26.145 --> 00:27:27.379
It proves she knew
Raiden worked for her.

739
00:27:27.479 --> 00:27:28.715
That's the problem.

740
00:27:28.815 --> 00:27:30.249
At the last minute.
they pull out

741
00:27:30.382 --> 00:27:32.218
exactly what Raiden needs
to prove his case.

742
00:27:32.318 --> 00:27:34.220
I think he faked the email.

743
00:27:34.320 --> 00:27:37.790
Well. unless we can prove it.
Kyla's done.

744
00:27:41.460 --> 00:27:43.629
Marissa wants to see us.

745
00:27:43.763 --> 00:27:44.731
You okay?

746
00:27:44.831 --> 00:27:46.632
Someone took out my brain

747
00:27:46.766 --> 00:27:48.600
and replaced it
with broken glass.

748
00:27:48.735 --> 00:27:50.737
but other than that I'm good.

749
00:27:50.837 --> 00:27:52.338
What happened?

750
00:27:52.471 --> 00:27:53.840
Nothing.

751
00:27:53.973 --> 00:27:55.908
Just a little too much fun.

752
00:27:56.008 --> 00:27:57.509
Let's go.

753
00:28:01.080 --> 00:28:02.648
The email wasn't fabricated.

754
00:28:02.782 --> 00:28:04.751
It definitely came
from Kyla's computer.

755
00:28:04.851 --> 00:28:06.318
Well.
Raiden's a coder. right?

756
00:28:06.452 --> 00:28:08.120
Maybe he hacked her system.

757
00:28:08.254 --> 00:28:09.789
or whoever put him
up to this did.

758
00:28:09.922 --> 00:28:12.524
Uh. if I can find
evidence of a hack.

759
00:28:12.658 --> 00:28:14.526
I might be able to work
backwards to whoever did it.

760
00:28:14.660 --> 00:28:16.462
but I'll need access
to Kyla's servers.

761
00:28:16.595 --> 00:28:18.197
Well. they're at her house.
I can get you in.

762
00:28:18.330 --> 00:28:20.332
Danny. can you go with her?

763
00:28:20.466 --> 00:28:22.001
See if there are any signs
of a break-in.

764
00:28:22.134 --> 00:28:24.536
Someone may have tried to get
to the servers directly.

765
00:28:24.670 --> 00:28:25.671
Sure.

766
00:28:25.805 --> 00:28:26.806
Excuse me.

767
00:28:26.939 --> 00:28:28.474
Sorry to interrupt.
I'm. uh.

768
00:28:28.607 --> 00:28:29.708
looking for her.

769
00:28:29.842 --> 00:28:32.979
I'll check in with you both
later.

770
00:28:33.112 --> 00:28:34.947
What's up?
You. um...

771
00:28:35.047 --> 00:28:36.849
left your credit card
at the bar last night.

772
00:28:36.983 --> 00:28:39.351
Oh.

773
00:28:39.485 --> 00:28:40.686
Thanks.

774
00:28:40.820 --> 00:28:41.788
How'd you find me?

775
00:28:41.888 --> 00:28:43.322
You told me where you worked.

776
00:28:43.455 --> 00:28:44.891
Twice.

777
00:28:45.024 --> 00:28:46.859
Oh.
I wanted to make sure

778
00:28:46.993 --> 00:28:48.027
you're okay.

779
00:28:48.160 --> 00:28:49.361
since I couldn't get you
that cab.

780
00:28:49.495 --> 00:28:51.864
Yeah. I'm-I'm good.

781
00:28:51.998 --> 00:28:53.833
Thank you.

782
00:28:53.966 --> 00:28:55.167
How's the mysterious
shoulder injury treating you?

783
00:28:55.301 --> 00:28:56.168
You know. it's...

784
00:28:56.302 --> 00:28:57.203
it's better.

785
00:28:57.336 --> 00:28:58.570
It's getting better.

786
00:29:00.572 --> 00:29:01.473
Okay then.

787
00:29:01.573 --> 00:29:03.142
I'll. uh...

788
00:29:03.242 --> 00:29:05.044
I'll go. I guess.

789
00:29:10.549 --> 00:29:13.152
You ever hear
the phrase "climbing heavy"?

790
00:29:13.252 --> 00:29:14.220
No.

791
00:29:14.353 --> 00:29:15.855
It's when a climber's having

792
00:29:15.988 --> 00:29:17.389
a tougher time with a route
than they should be.

793
00:29:17.523 --> 00:29:19.525
They're out of shape.
or their head's not in it.

794
00:29:19.658 --> 00:29:20.860
Usually because
they're distracted

795
00:29:20.993 --> 00:29:21.928
by something.

796
00:29:22.061 --> 00:29:23.695
Are you saying that's me?

797
00:29:23.830 --> 00:29:25.264
You looked that way last night.

798
00:29:25.397 --> 00:29:26.432
For whatever it's worth.

799
00:29:28.067 --> 00:29:29.035
Anyway.

800
00:29:29.168 --> 00:29:30.402
you got your card.

801
00:29:30.536 --> 00:29:31.737
See you.

802
00:29:35.674 --> 00:29:38.244
♪

803
00:29:38.377 --> 00:29:40.279
Um. we should
get to Kyla's house.

804
00:29:40.412 --> 00:29:42.048
Absolutely.

805
00:29:45.351 --> 00:29:46.618
Checked all the entrances

806
00:29:46.752 --> 00:29:48.387
and the. uh. security footage.

807
00:29:48.520 --> 00:29:49.856
There's no sign
anyone broke in.

808
00:29:49.956 --> 00:29:51.190
How are you doing?

809
00:29:51.290 --> 00:29:53.225
I'm fighting
with the bloody smart sensors

810
00:29:53.359 --> 00:29:55.862
bloody Kyla and Oscar
installed everywhere

811
00:29:55.962 --> 00:29:58.597
in this bloody house
that for some bloody reason

812
00:29:58.730 --> 00:30:01.600
don't want me to have
access to the servers.

813
00:30:01.733 --> 00:30:03.569
Smart sensors?

814
00:30:03.702 --> 00:30:06.238
They track your heartbeat.
insulin level.

815
00:30:06.372 --> 00:30:07.974
Practically read your mind.
I'd think they were amazing

816
00:30:08.107 --> 00:30:09.708
if they weren't making me
so miserable.

817
00:30:09.808 --> 00:30:11.410
Oh.

818
00:30:11.543 --> 00:30:13.579
Who was that guy today?

819
00:30:14.947 --> 00:30:16.382
Bartender from last night.

820
00:30:17.283 --> 00:30:18.650
Pretty sweet as bartenders go.

821
00:30:18.784 --> 00:30:20.586
Bringing you your card and all.

822
00:30:21.587 --> 00:30:22.621
Yep.

823
00:30:23.589 --> 00:30:24.590
Seems like a nice guy.

824
00:30:24.723 --> 00:30:26.225
Can we just not talk about him?

825
00:30:26.325 --> 00:30:28.594
Can we not talk
about anything?

826
00:30:28.727 --> 00:30:30.897
Can we just do the job
and not talk?
Fine.

827
00:30:30.997 --> 00:30:32.164
We don't have to talk about it.

828
00:30:32.298 --> 00:30:33.632
but when even bartenders
are asking

829
00:30:33.765 --> 00:30:35.467
if you're okay.
you might take the hint.

830
00:30:35.601 --> 00:30:37.003
You don't look good.

831
00:30:37.136 --> 00:30:38.504
I don't know what's going on.
but something is.

832
00:30:38.637 --> 00:30:39.972
and you should talk to somebody
about it.

833
00:30:40.106 --> 00:30:41.173
Because this whole "I'm Danny.

834
00:30:41.307 --> 00:30:43.109
nothing bothers me" thing
is bull.

835
00:30:43.242 --> 00:30:45.777
And I know it sounds like it.
but I don't mean that as a pun.

836
00:30:46.745 --> 00:30:48.414
I'm sorry.

837
00:30:49.415 --> 00:30:51.117
I didn't mean to...

838
00:30:51.250 --> 00:30:53.519
I-I'm just hungover.

839
00:30:53.652 --> 00:30:55.287
Whatever you say.

840
00:31:02.528 --> 00:31:04.196
This is weird.

841
00:31:04.330 --> 00:31:05.864
What?

842
00:31:05.998 --> 00:31:08.367
I'm not seeing
any signs of a hack. but...

843
00:31:08.500 --> 00:31:11.337
look at the sensor readings
when the email was sent.

844
00:31:11.470 --> 00:31:14.140
See Kyla's heartbeat?
It's under 60 beats per minute.

845
00:31:14.273 --> 00:31:15.707
She was asleep.

846
00:31:16.775 --> 00:31:18.777
That means Marissa was right.
She couldn't have sent it.

847
00:31:18.877 --> 00:31:20.947
Uh-huh.
But look at Oscar's.

848
00:31:21.047 --> 00:31:22.848
120?

849
00:31:22.982 --> 00:31:25.384
He's not just awake.
he's jacked up.

850
00:31:25.517 --> 00:31:26.452
We've been looking
for the person

851
00:31:26.552 --> 00:31:27.853
who put Raiden up to it.

852
00:31:27.987 --> 00:31:29.655
maybe he's been under our nose
the whole time.

853
00:31:29.788 --> 00:31:31.657
We got to find something that
connects Raiden and Oscar.

854
00:31:31.790 --> 00:31:33.960
You think Oscar wrote the email?

855
00:31:34.060 --> 00:31:35.461
Our investigators discovered

856
00:31:35.561 --> 00:31:38.230
that Oscar and Raiden
know each other.

857
00:31:38.364 --> 00:31:40.466
Oscar was a professor in
Raiden's study abroad program.

858
00:31:40.566 --> 00:31:42.868
Study abroad.
That was over 20 years ago.

859
00:31:43.002 --> 00:31:44.370
They were also
at the same tech conference

860
00:31:44.503 --> 00:31:46.038
in Vegas

861
00:31:46.172 --> 00:31:49.208
a month before Raiden started
working for Moore House.

862
00:31:49.341 --> 00:31:50.309
And sleeping with you.

863
00:31:50.409 --> 00:31:51.310
You think they

864
00:31:51.410 --> 00:31:52.578
bumped into each other.

865
00:31:52.711 --> 00:31:54.880
started reminiscing
about old times.

866
00:31:55.014 --> 00:31:56.215
and then. what.

867
00:31:56.348 --> 00:31:58.250
decided to ruin my life for fun?

868
00:31:58.384 --> 00:32:00.919
Oscar knew when you would be
at the Siren Room.

869
00:32:01.053 --> 00:32:03.022
He knows Auden is
your favorite poet.

870
00:32:03.155 --> 00:32:04.690
He knows all your passwords.

871
00:32:04.823 --> 00:32:05.924
No. There's got to be
another explanation.

872
00:32:06.058 --> 00:32:07.526
It doesn't make any sense.

873
00:32:07.659 --> 00:32:10.596
If I pay. Oscar pays.

874
00:32:10.729 --> 00:32:12.231
But the board just gave him
your job.

875
00:32:12.364 --> 00:32:14.933
My husband loves me.

876
00:32:15.067 --> 00:32:17.069
He started out as your mentor.

877
00:32:17.203 --> 00:32:19.205
Now he's in your shadow. Kyla.

878
00:32:19.338 --> 00:32:22.241
Oscar would never.
never do this to me!

879
00:32:27.913 --> 00:32:29.781
Are you sure you're gonna
be okay without me?

880
00:32:29.915 --> 00:32:33.185
Oh. yeah. You go
and dance the night away.

881
00:32:33.285 --> 00:32:35.121
I've...

882
00:32:35.254 --> 00:32:36.955
Wait a second.

883
00:32:37.089 --> 00:32:39.625
Are you sure you can't just
stay home and take care of me?

884
00:32:39.758 --> 00:32:41.227
Anybody missing
a bucket of hot wings?

885
00:32:41.360 --> 00:32:43.462
Oh. in here.

886
00:32:43.595 --> 00:32:45.531
These were right
outside your door.

887
00:32:45.631 --> 00:32:46.532
Which was wide open?

888
00:32:46.632 --> 00:32:48.634
Well. I was worried that

889
00:32:48.767 --> 00:32:50.969
I wouldn't be able to get
to the door. so...

890
00:32:51.103 --> 00:32:52.638
I thought these wings were
supposed to come

891
00:32:52.771 --> 00:32:54.306
without judgment.

892
00:32:54.440 --> 00:32:56.108
I assume this isn't
a social call.

893
00:32:56.242 --> 00:32:57.809
We showed Kyla the evidence.

894
00:32:57.943 --> 00:32:58.977
but she refuses to believe it.

895
00:32:59.111 --> 00:33:00.379
Won't let us use it.

896
00:33:00.479 --> 00:33:01.713
And we're sunk if we
can't show the jury

897
00:33:01.813 --> 00:33:03.582
that Oscar put Raiden
up to this.

898
00:33:03.715 --> 00:33:05.317
Kyla's husband is behind this?

899
00:33:06.218 --> 00:33:08.054
I'm looking better
and better. aren't I?

900
00:33:08.154 --> 00:33:10.889
I know this is a horrible thing
for Kyla to have to accept.

901
00:33:10.989 --> 00:33:12.324
but the evidence is
pretty clear.

902
00:33:12.458 --> 00:33:13.592
I don't know
how else to prove it to her.

903
00:33:13.725 --> 00:33:15.394
Mind if I get that...

904
00:33:15.494 --> 00:33:17.796
Yes. I do.
When Jason was accused of
jury tampering.

905
00:33:17.929 --> 00:33:19.565
there's no evidence

906
00:33:19.665 --> 00:33:21.133
that would've convinced me
he was guilty.

907
00:33:21.267 --> 00:33:23.469
He would've had to
confess to me himself.

908
00:33:24.470 --> 00:33:26.838
Well. then. I guess you're gonna
have to get Oscar to confess.

909
00:33:26.972 --> 00:33:29.775
♪

910
00:33:36.448 --> 00:33:37.649
You really believe this?

911
00:33:37.783 --> 00:33:39.451
Because of an
elevated heart rate

912
00:33:39.585 --> 00:33:43.355
and some decades-old
study abroad trip?

913
00:33:43.489 --> 00:33:45.257
I don't even remember the guy.

914
00:33:45.357 --> 00:33:46.492
This is ridiculous.

915
00:33:46.625 --> 00:33:48.960
I assure you I am serious.

916
00:33:49.095 --> 00:33:52.164
You are facing charges of
conspiracy to commit fraud.

917
00:33:52.298 --> 00:33:53.165
identity theft.

918
00:33:53.299 --> 00:33:54.866
federal wire fraud.

919
00:33:55.000 --> 00:33:56.368
You could be looking at

920
00:33:56.502 --> 00:33:58.537
spending the rest of your life
behind bars.

921
00:34:06.312 --> 00:34:07.479
What's Raiden doing here?

922
00:34:07.613 --> 00:34:08.880
Chunk reached out
to a friend of his

923
00:34:09.014 --> 00:34:10.048
who works in the D.A.'s office.

924
00:34:10.182 --> 00:34:11.317
He's on his way over.

925
00:34:11.450 --> 00:34:13.385
Whoever talks first
will get immunity

926
00:34:13.519 --> 00:34:14.853
in exchange for testifying

927
00:34:14.986 --> 00:34:16.322
against their coconspirator.

928
00:34:16.455 --> 00:34:18.357
Yeah. well. I'm not talking

929
00:34:18.490 --> 00:34:20.559
because there's nothing to say.

930
00:34:20.692 --> 00:34:21.560
Do you trust Raiden

931
00:34:21.693 --> 00:34:23.729
to keep his mouth shut

932
00:34:23.862 --> 00:34:27.133
when he learns how many years
he could spend in prison?

933
00:34:29.735 --> 00:34:32.504
I thought we were here
to discuss a new settlement.

934
00:34:32.638 --> 00:34:35.641
Did I say that?
I'm sorry. No.

935
00:34:35.741 --> 00:34:38.544
We are here because Raiden
and Oscar are gonna play a game

936
00:34:38.677 --> 00:34:40.078
of prisoner's dilemma.

937
00:34:40.212 --> 00:34:41.347
And if Raiden can win.

938
00:34:41.480 --> 00:34:42.481
he might be able
to avoid prison.

939
00:34:42.581 --> 00:34:44.150
What are you talking about?

940
00:34:44.250 --> 00:34:45.751
You want to tell her about
the conspiracy you have

941
00:34:45.884 --> 00:34:48.354
with Oscar Moore.
or should I?

942
00:34:49.921 --> 00:34:51.390
You know me.

943
00:34:53.225 --> 00:34:55.227
I love Kyla.

944
00:34:55.361 --> 00:34:57.363
How could you ever think

945
00:34:57.496 --> 00:35:00.532
that I would do
something so cruel?

946
00:35:00.666 --> 00:35:02.701
I think you were hurt.

947
00:35:03.935 --> 00:35:06.405
And you wanted her
to hurt. too.

948
00:35:07.406 --> 00:35:09.275
What was it?

949
00:35:09.408 --> 00:35:11.743
That her ideas
always eclipsed yours?

950
00:35:12.911 --> 00:35:14.446
That she got
all the attention?

951
00:35:14.580 --> 00:35:16.548
Were you sick of just being
Kyla Moore's husband?

952
00:35:18.417 --> 00:35:19.885
Was I even that?

953
00:35:21.553 --> 00:35:25.056
My wife was sleeping
with other men.

954
00:35:25.191 --> 00:35:28.694
Because she thought you wanted
to sleep with other women.

955
00:35:28.794 --> 00:35:30.562
She was trying to save
your marriage.

956
00:35:30.696 --> 00:35:34.466
Then she should have
let me be the man

957
00:35:34.600 --> 00:35:36.067
for once.

958
00:35:42.941 --> 00:35:45.411
He resented me that much?

959
00:35:45.544 --> 00:35:47.045
I'm so sorry.

960
00:35:48.447 --> 00:35:50.048
Was I supposed to make
myself smaller

961
00:35:50.148 --> 00:35:51.717
to make him feel bigger?
No.

962
00:35:51.817 --> 00:35:53.919
You should never do that.

963
00:35:56.755 --> 00:35:58.324
What can I do to help?

964
00:36:02.261 --> 00:36:03.562
Shut it down.

965
00:36:03.662 --> 00:36:05.731
We're talking to
the D.A.'s office.
No.

966
00:36:05.831 --> 00:36:08.967
I don't want the world to know
my own husband tried to ruin me.

967
00:36:10.436 --> 00:36:12.504
Are you saying that you don't
want Oscar to be punished

968
00:36:12.638 --> 00:36:14.306
for what he's done to you?

969
00:36:17.108 --> 00:36:19.578
I just want you
to make it go away.

970
00:36:24.182 --> 00:36:25.517
Your Honor.

971
00:36:25.651 --> 00:36:28.019
my client would like to
withdraw his complaint.

972
00:36:28.153 --> 00:36:29.688
He has a statement
he'd like to make.

973
00:36:29.821 --> 00:36:31.490
if it please the court.

974
00:36:31.623 --> 00:36:32.858
Go ahead.

975
00:36:35.261 --> 00:36:38.364
The allegations I made against
Kyla Moore were not true.

976
00:36:39.665 --> 00:36:41.767
She never sexually harassed me.

977
00:36:42.768 --> 00:36:44.770
I'd like to apologize to her

978
00:36:44.870 --> 00:36:45.971
and her family

979
00:36:46.104 --> 00:36:47.973
for putting them
through this ordeal.

980
00:36:48.106 --> 00:36:50.642
And I'd also like to
apologize to the court.

981
00:36:50.776 --> 00:36:52.878
Mr. Parks.

982
00:36:53.011 --> 00:36:55.046
are you admitting
that you committed perjury

983
00:36:55.180 --> 00:36:56.482
in my courtroom?

984
00:36:57.649 --> 00:36:59.651
Your Honor. if I may be heard?

985
00:36:59.785 --> 00:37:01.353
I suppose so.

986
00:37:01.487 --> 00:37:04.390
Ms. Moore would like to put
this unpleasant chapter

987
00:37:04.523 --> 00:37:06.658
behind her
as soon as possible.

988
00:37:06.792 --> 00:37:08.193
I've spoken
with the D.A.'s office.

989
00:37:08.327 --> 00:37:09.895
and we've worked out a deal

990
00:37:10.028 --> 00:37:12.298
whereby Mr. Parks
would do 200 hours

991
00:37:12.398 --> 00:37:13.699
of community service
in exchange

992
00:37:13.832 --> 00:37:16.134
for pleading guilty to perjury.

993
00:37:16.234 --> 00:37:18.670
We don't want to waste
any more of the court's time.

994
00:37:22.040 --> 00:37:23.709
Mr. Parks.

995
00:37:23.842 --> 00:37:25.911
you got off easy.

996
00:37:26.044 --> 00:37:27.413
But you had better hope

997
00:37:27.546 --> 00:37:29.381
that I never see you
in my courtroom again.

998
00:37:32.083 --> 00:37:33.519
This case is adjourned.

999
00:37:46.231 --> 00:37:47.599
I'm supposed to be dead.

1000
00:37:48.834 --> 00:37:50.836
Funny. You don't look dead.

1001
00:37:51.870 --> 00:37:54.840
A guy pointed a gun
at my head.

1002
00:37:54.940 --> 00:37:57.275
pulled the trigger...

1003
00:37:58.377 --> 00:37:59.511
That's supposed to kill you.

1004
00:37:59.611 --> 00:38:01.212
But it didn't.

1005
00:38:01.347 --> 00:38:02.714
Nope.

1006
00:38:02.848 --> 00:38:04.550
The gun misfired.

1007
00:38:05.617 --> 00:38:06.552
Here I am.

1008
00:38:06.685 --> 00:38:09.187
That's a good thing. Right?

1009
00:38:09.287 --> 00:38:10.422
Considering the alternative.

1010
00:38:11.423 --> 00:38:12.591
Yeah.

1011
00:38:12.724 --> 00:38:14.059
I guess.

1012
00:38:16.395 --> 00:38:18.630
I just. I haven't felt right
about it since it happened.

1013
00:38:18.764 --> 00:38:20.298
and I can't talk to my friends
about it.

1014
00:38:20.432 --> 00:38:21.700
Why not?

1015
00:38:22.734 --> 00:38:24.936
I need something to be
different.

1016
00:38:26.872 --> 00:38:30.642
If I got a second chance
for whatever reason.

1017
00:38:30.776 --> 00:38:33.645
something's got to change.

1018
00:38:33.779 --> 00:38:36.247
My life. my-my job.

1019
00:38:36.382 --> 00:38:37.449
Something.

1020
00:38:37.583 --> 00:38:40.151
Then why are you telling me?

1021
00:38:40.285 --> 00:38:42.287
Dude. I don't know.
You climbed Everest.

1022
00:38:43.922 --> 00:38:45.991
I only got halfway.

1023
00:38:46.124 --> 00:38:47.593
But...

1024
00:38:47.726 --> 00:38:49.294
I think I've got something
that will help.

1025
00:38:55.601 --> 00:38:57.002
You're-you're giving me coffee?

1026
00:38:57.135 --> 00:38:58.269
Oh. do not tell me

1027
00:38:58.404 --> 00:38:59.771
you're a tea person.

1028
00:38:59.905 --> 00:39:01.840
No. this is. this is good.

1029
00:39:05.243 --> 00:39:06.445
What's this?

1030
00:39:06.578 --> 00:39:09.180
This is a topo map
of Mount Marcy.

1031
00:39:09.314 --> 00:39:10.682
It's up in the Adirondacks.

1032
00:39:10.816 --> 00:39:12.684
A few of us are climbing it
this weekend.

1033
00:39:12.818 --> 00:39:14.586
It's not exactly

1034
00:39:14.686 --> 00:39:17.456
Mount Everest--
pretty easy walk-- but...

1035
00:39:17.589 --> 00:39:18.524
from the peak

1036
00:39:18.657 --> 00:39:19.991
you can see for miles.

1037
00:39:20.125 --> 00:39:22.528
It's like the whole world's laid
at your feet.

1038
00:39:24.262 --> 00:39:25.764
You want to come along?

1039
00:39:26.832 --> 00:39:28.834
I don't know your name.

1040
00:39:28.967 --> 00:39:30.335
It's Cameron.

1041
00:39:30.469 --> 00:39:32.270
Danny.

1042
00:39:32.370 --> 00:39:34.039
I know.
I saw your credit card.

1043
00:39:34.172 --> 00:39:35.607
- Right.
- Cameron!

1044
00:39:35.707 --> 00:39:39.545
Oh. um. I got to get this guy.
but. uh...

1045
00:39:39.678 --> 00:39:41.547
think about it.

1046
00:39:43.615 --> 00:39:47.519
♪ Completely caught up

1047
00:39:47.653 --> 00:39:50.556
♪ Next stop. shook up ♪

1048
00:39:52.524 --> 00:39:55.160
♪ The one to blame is you... ♪

1049
00:39:55.293 --> 00:39:58.864
Well. Oscar's the one
who got off easy. if you ask me.

1050
00:39:58.997 --> 00:40:00.966
In six months.
Kyla will file for divorce.

1051
00:40:01.066 --> 00:40:03.401
and Oscar will
step down as CFO.

1052
00:40:03.535 --> 00:40:06.171
And he'll be riding out his time
in their house in Aspen.

1053
00:40:06.304 --> 00:40:07.906
It's a gilded prison.

1054
00:40:08.039 --> 00:40:10.408
I bet you wish
he was behind real bars.

1055
00:40:10.542 --> 00:40:12.310
This is what Kyla wants.

1056
00:40:12.410 --> 00:40:14.546
Her heart's broken.
but at least she walks away

1057
00:40:14.680 --> 00:40:16.515
with her dignity intact.

1058
00:40:16.648 --> 00:40:18.083
Yeah.

1059
00:40:18.216 --> 00:40:20.251
At least someone got
to keep their dignity.

1060
00:40:21.720 --> 00:40:25.090
Those muscle relaxers
were powerful.

1061
00:40:25.223 --> 00:40:27.158
Was it as bad as I remember?
It wasn't so...

1062
00:40:27.258 --> 00:40:28.527
Worse.

1063
00:40:28.660 --> 00:40:30.061
Hmm.

1064
00:40:30.195 --> 00:40:31.162
Well. thank you for keeping
the ship afloat

1065
00:40:31.262 --> 00:40:32.698
while I was lost at sea.

1066
00:40:33.932 --> 00:40:36.768
You know. I forgot how good it
feels to just stand up straight.

1067
00:40:36.902 --> 00:40:38.504
I'm gonna go try the stairs.

1068
00:40:38.604 --> 00:40:39.771
See you in the morning.

1069
00:40:39.905 --> 00:40:41.339
See ya.

1070
00:40:46.377 --> 00:40:49.447
You ever think we could run
this place on our own?

1071
00:40:49.581 --> 00:40:52.250
Oh. yeah. Definitely.

1072
00:40:52.383 --> 00:40:54.620
And with a better name
than TAC.

1073
00:40:54.753 --> 00:40:56.755
Actually. TAC was my idea.

1074
00:40:57.723 --> 00:41:00.692
And by better.
I mean TAC is perfect.

1075
00:41:00.792 --> 00:41:03.128
What were you thinking?
No.

1076
00:41:03.261 --> 00:41:04.796
TAC's great.

1077
00:41:04.930 --> 00:41:05.964
Really.

1078
00:41:08.634 --> 00:41:10.468
It was nice working with you.
friend.

1079
00:41:10.602 --> 00:41:11.970
Right back at you.

